          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".IN THE DETERMINATION OF RESONANCE PARAMETERS FROM A",
                " COMBINATION OF THE RESULTS FROM TWO INDEPENDENT",
                " EXPERIMENTS (FISSION AND TOTAL CROSS-SECTION), IT IS",
                " ESSENTIAL THAT THE E(N) SCALE IN THE TWO EXPERIMENTS",
                " AGREE. THE ENERGY SCALE BY JAMES AND RAE,(NUCL.PHYS.",
                " A118,(68)313) IS INCORRECT AT HIGH ENERGY AND A NEW",
                " SCALE HAS BEEN ADOPTED WHICH IS CORRECT FOR ALUMINIUM",
                " RESONANCE AT 35.4 KEV WHILE MAINTAINING U-234",
                " RESONANCE AT 5.19 EV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".THE FISSION WIDTH DEDUCED FOR AN ASSUMED CONST-VALUE",
                " OF RADIATION WIDTH = 25 MILLI-EV.",
                ".FISSION WIDTHS COULD BE OBTAINED FOR 38 LEVELS BELOW",
                " 686.7 EV. EXCEPT LAST TWO OF THESE LEVELS IT WAS",
                " POSSIBLE TO REDUCE THE ERROR IN FISSION WIDTH FROM THE",
                " ERRORS IN NEUTRON WIDTH AND SIGZERO*G(F). BUT FOR THE",
                " TWO LEVELS AT 638.4 EV AND 686.7 EV THE LOWER LIMIT TO",
                " G(N) IS ZERO AND THIS DOES NOT GIVE AN UPPER BOUND TO",
                " G(F). IN THESE TWO CASES, THE UPPER LIMIT TO G(F) IS",
                " TAKEN AS THE OBSERVED RESONANCE WIDTH MINUS THE WIDTH",
                " OF RESOLUTION FUNCTION CALCULATED."
              ]
            }
          ],
